# UI Debugging Rule (Prefer Agent Browser)

## Core Principle

- For UI/UX bugs and investigations requiring on-screen reproduction, **prioritize agent-browser**
- Try agent-browser before other browser tools (MCP chrome-devtools, playwright)
- Iterate rapidly between screen and source code: **reproduce -> hypothesize cause -> fix -> re-verify**

## agent-browser Advantages

| Feature | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **AI optimized** | `snapshot -i -c` returns element references (`@e1`, `@e2`) |
| **Simple** | Direct CLI execution, no MCP needed |
| **Fast** | Rust-based binary |
| **Session management** | Manage multiple tabs in parallel with `--session` |

## Recommended Approach

### 1. Define Reproduction Conditions

- Document the target URL, user state (login/permissions/data), expected vs actual behavior

### 2. Reproduce with agent-browser

```bash
# Open the page
agent-browser open https://example.com/target-page

# Get AI-friendly snapshot (interactive elements only)
agent-browser snapshot -i -c

# Example output:
# - button "Login" [ref=e1]
# - input "Email" [ref=e2]
# - input "Password" [ref=e3]
```

### 3. Execute Actions to Reproduce the Issue

```bash
# Click using element reference
agent-browser click @e1

# Fill in forms
agent-browser fill @e2 "test@example.com"
agent-browser fill @e3 "password123"

# Check state
agent-browser snapshot -i -c
```

### 4. Observe -> Hypothesize -> Check Code

- Use snapshot/screenshot/console log data to narrow down candidate causes
- Check related source (UI/state management/API/validation)

### 5. Apply Minimal Fix

- Keep the change scope small, ensure the fix's intent and side effects are explainable

### 6. Re-verify with agent-browser

```bash
# Confirm the issue no longer reproduces with the same steps
agent-browser open https://example.com/target-page
agent-browser snapshot -i -c
agent-browser click @e1
# ...
```

## Fallback When agent-browser is Unavailable

Try alternatives in this order:

1. **MCP browser tools** (chrome-devtools, playwright)
2. **Manual reproduction**:
   - Reproduction steps (URL/actions/expected/actual)
   - Screenshots/videos
   - Console logs/network logs
3. **Automated E2E**:
   - If possible, add a minimal Playwright/Cypress test to prevent regression

## Common Commands

```bash
# Basic operations
agent-browser open <url>          # Open page
agent-browser snapshot -i -c      # Snapshot (AI-friendly)
agent-browser click @e1           # Click
agent-browser fill @e2 "text"     # Fill input
agent-browser screenshot out.png  # Screenshot

# Debugging
agent-browser --headed open <url> # Open with visible browser
agent-browser console             # Show console logs
agent-browser errors              # Show page errors

# Information retrieval
agent-browser get text @e1        # Get text
agent-browser get html @e1        # Get HTML
agent-browser get url             # Get current URL
```
